properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued February 11 at 10:11AM EST until February 12 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Dense fog will reduce visibility to one to two miles.

* WHERE...All nearshore Gulf waters.

* WHEN...Until 7 AM EST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Low visibility will make navigation difficult.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...This advisory will likely needed to be
extended past 12z on Wednesday. Although it may not be 1 mile or
less the entire time, it will be widespread enough in time and
location to warrant the long duration advisory.
properties.instruction:
If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 AM EST WEDNESDAY
